= Example Blocks

Example blocks are used to display example content with normal substitutions applied.

== Basic Example Block

====
This is an example block.

It can contain *bold* and _italic_ text, as well as other formatting.

Example blocks are useful for demonstrating concepts or showing sample output.
====

== Example Block with Title

.Example: Sample Output
====
User logged in successfully
Session ID: abc123
Timestamp: 2024-01-01 12:00:00
====

== Example Block with ID

[#example-1]
.Example: Configuration
====
server {
  listen 80;
  server_name example.com;
  root /var/www/html;
}
====

